entry.title: Move ownership of sockets to QuicChromiumPacketReaders
entry.content:
Packet readers and sockets have a 1:1 relationship i.e. every socket

has a reader and each reader is associated with a socket it reads from.

Hence, to simplify the ownership and socket lifetime, we create the

packet reader with the socket, and use it to access the socket whenever

that is needed. This ensures that the list of sockets and

packet readers do not go out of sync.

entry.title: Default phone numbers to national numbers
entry.content:
Currently our local heuristics classify simple phone number forms as

PHONE_HOME_WHOLE_NUMBER (i.e. an international phone number starting

with + country code), while our crowdsourcing prefers

PHONE_HOME_CITY_AND_NUMBER.



With the feature kAutofillDefaultToCityAndNumber, the local heuristics

follow the same strategy as crowdsourcing, except if we find a "+" in

the field label as that may indicate an example to the user (like "+49

...").

entry.title: BRP: Force developers to use the facade header for raw_*.
entry.content:
To make PartitionAlloc usable as a library, I am going to move its

location. Unfortunately, developers are very frequently using the direct

header to import it. This happens daily. This patch adds a BanRule to

ask them to use the facade instead.



Alternatively, we could us GN visibility rules to allow only "base" from

depending directly on "partition_alloc". For now, I ignored this option,

because partition_alloc is used by pdfium, and other third_parties will

be added. I think it would be nice to separate partition_alloc into a

public and private parts first, if we want to going into this direction.

change (e.g., going into "tab overview"). The custom lifecycle ignores

page navigations.



After this change, the VCN enrollment bottom sheet does not dismiss on

page navigation.

entry.title: [iOS] Implement HistorySyncPopupCoordinator interrupt
entry.content:
This patch implements interrupt method.

If the interrupt requires the view to be dismissed:

1- Dismiss the view

2- Call the delegate

3- Call the interrupt completion block



If the interrupt is called for shutdown:

entry.title: [iOS][UNO] Undo changes to CBD strings
entry.content:
This reverts crrev.com/c/4753035 and crrev.com/c/4753453.



Those CLs added checks for kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos and, if

enabled, removed "synced" from the CBD strings. However, that was the

wrong thing to check: The "synced" label should still be added for

syncing users, no matter what the state of that feature is - it just

shouldn't be added for signed-in non-syncing users. And that's the

behavior of the code anyway, without any feature checks: The

entry.title: Add more functionality to set local password input element
entry.content:
This element asks the user to enter a local/device password and confirm

it. The element will be used during onboarding/OOBE and on the ChromeOS

settings page.



Previously the element contained only two password inputs and delegated

most functionality to its parent element. With this change, more

functionality resides in the input element:



- Placeholder and error tooltips are now hardcoded in the input

elements, since they're shared between OOBE and settings.

- The element now handles checking the the password complexity and that

the two user-entered values agree.

- The element now handles traversal between the two password inputs

itself, and only fires events when a password input is available

(i.e., when the user-entered password passes validation).



The commit also changes the name of the element from

local-password-input to set-local-password-input, since only the latter

communicates that the element asks for a new password and is not

suitable for asking the user for their existing password.



Screenshot: https://screenshot.googleplex.com/8WATn4b3Ci7LAL7

entry.title: [Feature] Added comparison for streets in profile subset check.
entry.content:
Autofill ignores street addresses while checking if a profile is a

subset of another profile. The reason was that street addresses could

exist in multiple formats and text normalization wouldn't be enough to

compare them.



This CL:

-Compares street addresses in `IsSubsetOfForFieldSet` using

`GetValueForComparisonForType`.

-Adds unit tests to test the difference between different street

addresses and different but equivalent street addresses.

-Puts the new functionality behind a Finch feature flag

kAutofillUseAddressRewritterInProfileSubsetComparison.
